<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870424-0006 </DOCNO><HL> Westcoast to Buy HoldingOf 54% in Oil and Gas Firm</HL><DD> 04/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WTC T.CNR T.HBCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> VANCOUVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Westcoast Transmission Co. said it agreed to buy a 54% stake in Canadian Roxy Petroleum Ltd., a unit of Hudson's Bay Co., for $82.7 million (Canadian).    Westcoast, which is involved mainly in natural gas transmission, said it will buy 7.5 million shares of the oil and gas company for $11 each from Hudson's, a department store chain.    The agreement is subject to approval of regulators and both companies' boards. Canadian Roxy had 13.9 million barrels of oil and natural gas liquids reserves and 137 billion cubic feet of proved and probable natural gas reserves as of Dec. 31. The company also has 366,000 net acres of exploratory properties, mainly in Alberta. </TEXT></DOC>